.TH TRANSCRIBE-DIARIZE 1 "February 2025" "parakeet-transcribe 0.3.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
transcribe-diarize \- transcribe with speaker identification
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B transcribe-diarize
.I audio.wav
.RI [ model_dir ]
.RI [ sortformer_dir ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B transcribe-diarize
transcribes audio and identifies who is speaking (up to 4 speakers).
Uses Parakeet TDT for transcription and Sortformer for speaker diarization.
.PP
Supports 25 languages (TDT). Diarization is language-independent.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I audio.wav
Path to audio file (required)
.TP
.I model_dir
Path to TDT model (default: /usr/share/parakeet-transcribe/tdt)
.TP
.I sortformer_dir
Path to Sortformer model (default: /usr/share/parakeet-transcribe/sortformer)
.SH OUTPUT
.PP
[0.00s - 2.50s] Speaker 0: Hello, how are you?
.br
[2.60s - 5.30s] Speaker 1: I'm fine, thanks!
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR transcribe (1),
.BR transcribe-stream-diarize (1)
.SH AUTHOR
rcspam <rcspams@gmail.com>
